  "body": "When doing a contract call (eth_call) with using a block number that is in the future a valid result is returned instead of an error message. \r\n\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nErigon version: 2021.12.02\r\n\r\nOS & Version: Linux / docker\r\n\r\nCommit hash : 1781181b7d970609c55b3243a7b7d620de3eaa2e\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nResult should be:\r\n`{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":123,\"error\":{\"code\":-32000,\"message\":\"header not found\"}}`\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nResult is:\r\n`{\"jsonrpc\":\"2.0\",\"id\":123,\"result\":\"0x\"}`\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n`curl --location --request POST 'erigon.node' --header 'Content-Type: application/json' --data-raw '{\"jsonrpc\": \"2.0\",\"method\": \"eth_call\",\"params\":[{\"to\": \"0x111111111117dC0aa78b770fA6A738034120C302\",\"data\": \"0x70a08231000000000000000000000000a09d1afae21bda81c06fd6de9bbd7c7ed7b6dfb1\"},\"0xD59F80\"],\"id\":123}'`",
